news.title: JSW Paints plans to double its revenue to Rs 2,000 crore in FY23
news.para: Achieving that revenue target will also help the company break into profitability in the decorative paints business, AS Sundaresan, chief executive officer, JSW Paints, told ET. Its industrial coatings business is already profitable, he said.

news.title: Maharashtra government may pay two years' rent to SRA & Mhada tenants
news.para: Deputy CM Devendra Fadnavis ​said there were also plans for redevelopment of properties affected by height restrictions in the airport funnel zone by exploring the floating FSI alternative, and refurbishment of tenanted buildings over 40 years old.

news.title: Lenders set to recover settlement amount for Reliance Home Finances
news.para: The Delhi High Court on December 21 vacated a stay on the distribution of proceeds from the sale of RHFL after two disputing creditors - a Shapoorji Pallonji entity and lenders led by Bank of Baroda - agreed on a 'conditional settlement'.

news.title: Supertech passing on YEIDA's Rs 90 crore land dues on us: UpCountry buyers
news.para: The aggrieved buyers plan to stage a protest outside the developer’s office in Sector 96 on Tuesday against the “illegitimate” demand as the latter “has already taken money from them over the years”.

news.title: UP-RERA authorises builder to complete Elegant Splendour, to monitor construction
news.para: Elegant Splendour project has two phases in which ‘Phase 1’ comprises of towers E, F and G towers and ‘Phase 3’ comprises towers A, B, C, D and H towers. The project was registered in UP RERA in August 2017 but could not be completed within the period of valid registration.

news.title: LIC Housing hikes lending rate by 0.35%, home loans to cost 8.65% now
news.para: In a statement, the company said it has increased the LIC Housing Prime Lending Rate (LHPLR), to which the interest rate on its loans is linked, by 0.35 per cent.

news.title: NGT extends stay on ministry of environment's notification on construction projects
news.para: The tribunal was hearing a petition which said the modified EIA regime, where the appraisal of impact assessment was not being done by SEIAAs, was against the principles of sustainable development and precautionary principles.

news.title: Noida authority issues Rs 235 crore notice to DLF over Mall of India land compensation
news.para: The development comes in the backdrop of a Supreme Court order on May 5 in which it had directed the Noida Authority to ensure payment of compensation for the land to its previous owner Veerana Redyy.

news.title: Over 170 irregular colonies in eight districts to be regularized: Haryana CM
news.para: Khattar said 177 irregular colonies in eight districts of the state would be regularized. Two years back, 845 such colonies were identified by the state government, he said.

news.title: Sebi orders attachment of bank, demat accounts of Sahara group firm, Subrata Roy, others
news.para: ​The recovery proceedings against five entities -- Sahara India Real Estate Corporation, Subrata Roy, Ashok Roy Choudhary, Ravi Shanker Dubey and Vandana Bharrgava -- for Rs 6.42 crore, includes interest, all costs, charges and expenses, Sebi said in the attachment order.

news.title: High voltage LED tubes set to replace streetlights in Guntur
news.para: Commissioner Chekuri Keerthi has directed the engineering department to immediately replace all the lights on the main roads and junctions.

news.title: Kolkata's New Town map to be redrawn to shed panchayat tag of mouzas
news.para: It has been learned from sources that the office of the local BLRO, along with the North 24 Parganas district administration and NKDA, was working to come up with a rectification to exclude areas from the panchayat's jurisdiction.

news.title: WeWork India raises Rs 550 crore from funds managed by BPEA Credit
news.para: WeWork India claimed to have turned profitable this year and locked a revenue of Rs 1,300 crore this year-end. At present, the EBITDA jump is 250% from a loss of Rs 120 crore in CY21 to a profit of Rs 175 crore in CY22, it said in the release.

news.title: Handed over to MCG four months ago, but no infra revamp yet at Greenwood City
news.para: The colony was transferred to MCG on August 28. Moreover, the MCG hasn’t paid salaries to the maintenance agency staff, who have worked beyond the overlapping period—September 16, residents claim.

news.title: Realtors give fake notes as Rs 1 crore loan, held in Bengaluru
news.para: The accused are Manna Sharuna, 35, R Vishnuraj alias Vishnu, 26, residents of Dinnur Main Road near RT Nagar, and Praveen Kumar, 40, of Manjunathanagar in Ramamurthynagar. Three more suspects - Ashalatha Rao, Lakshman Rao and Tushar - are at large and efforts are on to arrest them.
